docs.abstract: Anthony Levandowski was charged with stealing driverless-car plans when he left Google to form a company, which Uber then acquired.
docs.snippet: Anthony Levandowski was charged with stealing driverless-car plans when he left Google to form a company, which Uber then acquired.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Anthony Levandowski, a star engineer who helped build Google’s autonomous vehicle unit, pleaded guilty on Thursday to stealing trade secrets from the internet giant.

headline.main: Former Uber Executive Pleads Guilty to Trade Theft
headline.print_headline: Ex-Executive At Uber Pleads Guilty to Theft In Google Case

docs.abstract: Investors are still looking to Washington for a large scale effort to help businesses and workers affected by the virus outbreak.
docs.snippet: Investors are still looking to Washington for a large scale effort to help businesses and workers affected by the virus outbreak.
docs.lead_paragraph: This briefing is no longer updating. Live coverage can be found here.

docs.abstract: In China, many rural students lack the connections or hardware to learn remotely. More nations will confront the same reality as the outbreak spreads.
docs.snippet: In China, many rural students lack the connections or hardware to learn remotely. More nations will confront the same reality as the outbreak spreads.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — Like hundreds of millions of other children worldwide, Liu Chenxinhao and Liu Chenxinyuan were getting used to doing class work online. After their elementary school closed because of the coronavirus outbreak, the brothers received their homework through a smartphone app.

headline.main: The Coronavirus Exposes Education’s Digital Divide
headline.print_headline: Crisis Bares Tech Divide In Education

docs.abstract: The Federal Reserve is rushing to support money market mutual funds, in a disconcerting repeat of the 2008 financial crisis.
docs.snippet: The Federal Reserve is rushing to support money market mutual funds, in a disconcerting repeat of the 2008 financial crisis.
docs.lead_paragraph: Just before midnight Wednesday, the Federal Reserve announced that it was offering emergency loans to help money market mutual funds, its latest effort to shore up the financial system.

headline.main: Why We Are Once Again Rescuing a ‘Safe’ Investment
headline.print_headline: Fed Comes to the Rescue Of Another ‘Safe’ Investment

docs.abstract: Gig companies promoted their flexible hours as an economic lifeline for workers. In the coronavirus outbreak, it has been anything but.
docs.snippet: Gig companies promoted their flexible hours as an economic lifeline for workers. In the coronavirus outbreak, it has been anything but.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — It was just after 11 a.m. last Wednesday when Jaime Maldonado, 51, pulled his rented Nissan into a lot outside San Francisco International Airport. He figured he had a long wait ahead — about two hours — before Lyft would ping him to pick up a passenger.

headline.print_headline: Promise of Gig Economy Sours Amid Pandemic

byline.original: By Kate Conger, Adam Satariano and Mike Isaac

docs.abstract: New filings for unemployment benefits rose 30 percent last week amid cutbacks and shutdowns over the coronavirus crisis.
docs.snippet: New filings for unemployment benefits rose 30 percent last week amid cutbacks and shutdowns over the coronavirus crisis.
docs.lead_paragraph: In an early sign of the coronavirus pandemic’s devastating impact on American workers, the Labor Department on Thursday reported a 30 percent increase in unemployment claims last week, one of the largest spikes on record.

headline.main: A Torrent of Job Losses Threatens to Overwhelm the U.S. Economy
headline.print_headline: Claims Surge As Employees Are Cut Loose

docs.abstract: After a string of primary losses, the Vermont senator turned to a news network his allies love to criticize.
docs.snippet: After a string of primary losses, the Vermont senator turned to a news network his allies love to criticize.
docs.lead_paragraph: Two weeks ago, in the bowels of a Las Vegas casino, Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont confronted the president of MSNBC, Phil Griffin, with a stern demand: Be fair to me.

headline.main: Bernie Sanders Had a Problem With MSNBC. Then Came Super Tuesday.
headline.print_headline: After Super Tuesday Losses, Sanders Embraces ‘Terrible’ MSNBC

byline.original: By Michael M. Grynbaum and John Koblin

docs.abstract: Companies buy insurance that usually pays out when they have to halt operations. But it’s usually because of physical damage, not outbreaks.
docs.snippet: Companies buy insurance that usually pays out when they have to halt operations. But it’s usually because of physical damage, not outbreaks.
docs.lead_paragraph: Two years ago Munich Re, the reinsurance giant, tried to start underwriting a new kind of insurance — one that would make a company whole if its business tanked in an epidemic. For months, there were no takers.

headline.main: Coronavirus Will Cost Businesses Billions. Insurance May Not Help.
headline.print_headline: Insurance May Not Help if Businesses Hemorrhage

docs.abstract: The Federal Reserve Bank of New York president, John C. Williams, said central banks were working in tandem to tackle the global economic threat.
docs.snippet: The Federal Reserve Bank of New York president, John C. Williams, said central banks were working in tandem to tackle the global economic threat.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve Bank of New York president, John C. Williams, made clear on Thursday evening that officials viewed the emergency rate cut they approved earlier this week as part of an international push to cushion the economy as the coronavirus threatens global growth.

headline.main: Fed Official Says Central Bankers Are Aligned in Coronavirus Response
headline.print_headline: Global Banks Are Aligned For Response, Fed Says

docs.abstract: The budget carrier was challenged by rising competition, Brexit and more recently the spread of coronavirus, and had sought government help.
docs.snippet: The budget carrier was challenged by rising competition, Brexit and more recently the spread of coronavirus, and had sought government help.
docs.lead_paragraph: Flybe, an ailing regional airline in Britain that was praised for flying into underserved corners of the country, ceased operations on Thursday after financial strains caused by coronavirus.

headline.main: Flybe, a British Regional Airline, Stops Flying
headline.print_headline: Budget Airline Serving Britain Is Shut Down By Coronavirus

byline.original: By Iliana Magra and Carlos Tejada
